It would be useful to show a button to jump to the first and the last page of the table in the pagination template. I recommend to change the template to following:

    
    ng.module('smart-table', []).run(['$templateCache', function ($templateCache) {
        $templateCache.put('template/smart-table/pagination.html',
            '<div class="pagination" ng-if="pages.length >= 2"><ul class="pagination">' +
            '<li ng-if="1!==pages[0]"><a ng-click="selectPage(1)">1...</a></li>' +
            '<li ng-repeat="page in pages" ng-class="{active: page==currentPage}"><a ng-click="selectPage(page)">{{page}}</a></li>' +
            '<li ng-if="numPages!==pages[pages.length - 1]"><a ng-click="selectPage(numPages)">...{{numPages}}</a></li>' +
            '</ul></div>');
    }]);

Hi, I think that according to the jsonapi specification (http://jsonapi.org/format/#document-meta), DELETE should return a meta object, but this library is returning a string.
Incorrect:
```{
  "meta": {
    "Object successful deleted"
  },
  "jsonapi": {
    "version": "1.0"
  }
}
```
Correct:
```{
  "meta": {
    "result": "Object successful deleted"
  },
  "jsonapi": {
    "version": "1.0"
  }
}
```

I was having problems using this lib until I figured this out.
Cheers.

pipenv lock not resolves extras deps in [dev-packages]

##### Describe your environment

1. OS Type: macOS
1. Python version: `Python 3.6.4`
1. Pipenv version: `pipenv, version 11.0.2`

##### Expected result

All dependencies are locked in PIpfile.lock

##### Actual result

setup.py
```
from setuptools import setup, find_packages

setup(
    name='test',
    version='0.0.1',
    packages=find_packages(),
    extras_require={
        'test': [
            'pytest',
        ],
    },
)
